flowchart TD
    Start([App launch]) --> OnCreate[onCreate: build UI and opportunistically request USB permission if Zebra device is present]
    OnCreate --> OnStart[onStart: register USB attach/detach and USB permission receiver]
    OnStart --> UsbGateNote[USB permission request is not an RFID init gate]
    UsbGateNote --> BtPerms{onPostResume: Bluetooth permissions granted?}
    BtPerms -->|No| RequestBt[Request BLUETOOTH_SCAN and BLUETOOTH_CONNECT]
    BtPerms -->|Yes| InitSdk[InitRfidSDK]
    RequestBt --> BtGrant{Permission callback grants both?}
    BtGrant -->|No| StopInit[Stop RFID init and show permission warning]
    BtGrant -->|Yes| InitFromCallback[Call RFIDHandler.onCreate]
    InitFromCallback --> InitSdk

    InitSdk --> InitMode{readers == null?}
    InitMode -->|Yes| StartInit[Set isInitializing and queue initializeReadersAsync]
    InitMode -->|No| QueueConnect[connectReader]

    StartInit --> UsbReaders[Try Readers with SERVICE_USB]
    UsbReaders --> UsbFound{USB readers available?}
    UsbFound -->|Yes| QueueConnect
    UsbFound -->|No| BtReaders[Dispose and rebuild Readers with BLUETOOTH]

    BtReaders --> BtFound{Bluetooth readers available?}
    BtFound -->|Yes| QueueConnect
    BtFound -->|No| NoReader[Show no-reader status and clear progress]

    QueueConnect --> Busy{isConnectionQueued or isConnecting?}
    Busy -->|Yes| DupSkip[Skip duplicate connect request]
    Busy -->|No| Connected{Already connected?}
    Connected -->|Yes| AlreadyConnected[Clear progress and keep current session]
    Connected -->|No| ConnectAsync[Queue connectReaderAsync on single-thread workQueue]

    ConnectAsync --> Available[Attach reader event handler and refresh available readers]
    Available --> Found{Readers available?}
    Found -->|No| NoReader
    Found -->|Yes| Select[Select preferred reader by current transport, else first reader]

    Select --> Connecting{isConnecting.compareAndSet false -> true?}
    Connecting -->|No| DupSkip
    Connecting -->|Yes| Connect["connectReaderAsync runs on workQueue\nand starts connectWithTimeout"]
    Connect --> ConnectWorker["connectWithTimeout runs reader.connect\nin a short-lived worker with 10s timeout"]
    ConnectWorker --> AlreadyRunning{Throws \"Already running\"?}
    AlreadyRunning -->|Yes| RetryConnect[Disconnect and retry connect]
    AlreadyRunning -->|No| ConnectResult{Connected?}
    RetryConnect --> ConnectResult
    ConnectWorker -->|Timeout| TimeoutMsg[Disconnect best-effort and show timeout status]
    TimeoutMsg --> FailMsg[Show connection failure status]
    ConnectResult -->|No| FailMsg
    ConnectResult -->|Yes| Configure[Configure trigger, tag, disconnect, and inventory events\nReset bIsReading and update transport flags]
    Configure --> Ready([Connected and ready])

    Ready --> Runtime{Runtime event}
    Runtime -->|onPostResume| ResumeInit[InitRfidSDK then RFIDHandler.onResume]
    Runtime -->|USB attached| UsbAttach[Destroy handler and re-init SDK]
    Runtime -->|USB detached| Recover[Destroy reader and show reconnect dialog]
    Runtime -->|RFID DISCONNECTION_EVENT while BT| RecoverBt[Destroy reader and show reconnect dialog]
    Runtime -->|Reader disappeared| ReaderGone[Disconnect, dispose, and show reconnect dialog]
    Runtime -->|Trigger pressed| Inventory[Start inventory if not already reading]
    Runtime -->|Trigger released| StopInv[Stop inventory]
    Runtime -->|Tag data| UpdateUi[Append tag data to UI]

    ResumeInit --> InitSdk
    UsbAttach --> InitSdk
    Inventory --> Ready
    StopInv --> Ready
    UpdateUi --> Ready

    Recover --> Choice{User choice}
    RecoverBt --> Choice
    ReaderGone --> Choice
    Choice -->|Connect Bluetooth| DelayBt[Schedule RFID re-init after 5 seconds]
    Choice -->|Wait for USB| WaitUsb[Wait for next USB attach broadcast]
    DelayBt --> InitSdk
    WaitUsb --> UsbAttach

